With the following spec: 

``` json
{
  "consumes": [
    "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
  ],
  "info": {
    "name": "formData test"
  },
  "paths": {
    "/testing": {
      "post": {
        "parameters": [
          {
            "in": "formData",
            "name": "names",
            "type": "string"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Success message"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "produces": [
    "application/json",
    "application/json; charset=utf-8"
  ],
  "swagger": "2.0"
}
```

generating a server from this one and than running it. Currently (latest tip e4c8b3c09d4ed2b35e6b77e57ab77169e56243fc) you will get: 

``` shell
$ curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" "http://127.0.0.1:8282/testing" -d 'names=test'
{"code":500,"message":"request Content-Type isn't multipart/form-data"}
$ # obviously this next one doesn't work as well
$ curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" "http://127.0.0.1:8282/testing" -d 'name=test'
{"code":415,"message":"unsupported media type \"multipart/form-data\", only [application/x-www-form-urlencoded] are allowed"}
```

This appears to be coming from the std lib and more accurately from the call at
`restapi/operations/post_testing_parameters.go:37`

